JOHANNESBURG - People Opposing Women Abuse (Powa) said that there's a war against women in South Africa. Powa was reacting to Singwa Namhla Mtwa's death. Mtwa was shot dead in her car at her home in Mthatha last month. Itâ€™s alleged that her boyfriend of 17 years was behind her killing. "I mean you still feel that the government is not doing enough. Us, as Powa, and other organisations, I think we are trying our best but alone we are not going to win in this fight - it's a fight, it's war against women. We need commitment from the government. We always talk about our policies that are in place but I think our problem is implementation," said Powa's Jeanette Sera.